@page "/platform"

<PageTitle>Platform - Justin Palmer</PageTitle>

<div class="container-fluid">
    <section class="hero" role="region" aria-labelledby="platform-title">
        <div class="hero-grid">
            <div>
                <span class="tag">Cloud platform view</span>
                <h1 id="platform-title" class="hero-title">Enterprise data platform blueprint</h1>
                <p class="hero-copy">
                    A practical, end-to-end blueprint for batch + event-driven ingestion, trusted data products,
                    and governed analytics with secure APIs and modern web apps.
                </p>
                <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                    <span class="chip">Batch + streaming</span>
                    <span class="chip">Data contracts</span>
                    <span class="chip">Quality + governance</span>
                    <span class="chip">Secure APIs</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="hero-panel">
                <h2 class="h5 mb-2">Delivery pillars</h2>
                <ul class="list-unstyled d-grid gap-2">
                    <li>Reliable batch + streaming ingestion.</li>
                    <li>Governed access, lineage, and data quality checks.</li>
                    <li>Analytics experiences designed for action.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Architecture layers</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
            Layered design that supports secure data services, scalable ingestion, and analytics-ready models.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-2">
            I treat each layer as a contract boundary with explicit SLAs, security controls, and observability.
            The goal is to keep ingestion, APIs, and analytics decoupled while preserving lineage and governance.
        </p>
        <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-4 reveal">
                <div class="tile h-100">
                    <div class="tile-title">Experience layer</div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Role-aware web apps (Blazor/React) with secure auth flows, caching, and performance tuning.
                        Focused on operational UX for analysts and admins.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Azure App Service + Entra ID, token caching, and client-side performance profiling.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        UI standards cover role-aware navigation, access-aware search, and audit-safe actions.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-4 reveal">
                <div class="tile h-100">
                    <div class="tile-title">API layer</div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        RESTful services with Swagger/OpenAPI, OAuth/OIDC, and policy-based access controls.
                        Versioned endpoints with clear contracts and telemetry.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        ASP.NET Core APIs with OpenAPI docs, API Management policies, and private endpoints.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Standard policies include rate limiting, data masking, and outbound allow-listing.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-4 reveal">
                <div class="tile h-100">
                    <div class="tile-title">Data layer</div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Curated lake/warehouse zones, optimized compute, and governed metadata with tuning.
                        Partitioning, statistics, and workload isolation for performance.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Data Lake Gen2, Synapse Dedicated Pools, Azure SQL, and metadata governance workflows.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Dimensional models and tabular structures ensure consistent analytics across domains.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card compact p-4 mt-3 reveal">
            <h3 class="h5">Key design decisions</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled d-grid gap-2 mb-0">
                <li>Data contracts and source-to-target mappings drive repeatable ingestion patterns.</li>
                <li>API security, private endpoints, and ingress/egress controls protect workloads.</li>
                <li>Domain-aligned models and semantic layers keep analytics consistent and performant.</li>
                <li>Shared observability standards ensure pipeline, API, and model telemetry stays consistent.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">End-to-end flow</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
            From source integration to governed analytics, each stage is designed for reliability and reuse.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-2">
            The flow emphasizes repeatability: every dataset has a contract, validation plan, and release checklist.
            Changes are versioned, and every stage emits telemetry for audit and troubleshooting.
        </p>
        <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-3 reveal">
                <div class="tile h-100">
                    <div class="tile-title">Ingest</div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Batch loads, streaming events, and API integrations with CDC and schema drift handling.
                        Retry logic, idempotency, and dead-letter handling built in.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        ADF orchestrations, Event Grid triggers, and Function app transforms.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Change windows, backfill plans, and replay strategies are defined per source.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-3 reveal">
                <div class="tile h-100">
                    <div class="tile-title">Curate</div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Validation, certification, and metadata management with automated quality checks.
                        Reconciliation, anomaly detection, and data profiling.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Quality rules, profiling, and certification metadata stored per dataset.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Exceptions are documented with ownership, remediation plans, and severity levels.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-3 reveal">
                <div class="tile h-100">
                    <div class="tile-title">Serve</div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        API-first data products, dimensional models, and analytics-ready marts with RLS.
                        Semantic layers optimized for reuse and governance.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Synapse SQL, Power BI semantic models, and RLS enforcement.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        SLAs define freshness, query latency, and availability for each product.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-3 reveal">
                <div class="tile h-100">
                    <div class="tile-title">Operate</div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        CI/CD, monitoring, alerting, and incident response with runbooks and SLAs.
                        Automated rollback and environment parity checks.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Azure DevOps pipelines, IaC validation, and telemetry dashboards.
                    </div>
                    <div class="tile-text">
                        Health dashboards tie ingestion metrics to business outcomes and compliance checks.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Analytics and governance</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
            Governance, data quality, and metadata management keep analytics trusted and auditable.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-2">
            Governance is embedded into the platform with defined ownership, data certification workflows,
            and automated quality gates that prevent untrusted data from reaching consumers.
        </p>
        <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6 reveal">
                <div class="card compact p-4 h-100">
                    <h3 class="h5">Data governance</h3>
                    <p>
                        Data quality, metadata management, and certification aligned to regulated domains.
                        RLS, access audits, and controlled data sharing.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-0 text-muted small">
                        Domain data stewards own certification; access granted through automated review workflows.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6 reveal">
                <div class="card compact p-4 h-100">
                    <h3 class="h5">Operations and automation</h3>
                    <p>
                        CI/CD pipelines, monitoring, and alerting to keep data products stable and trusted.
                        Infrastructure as code and environment compliance checks.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mb-0 text-muted small">
                        Blue/green deployments, rollback automation, and release validation gates.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row g-3 mt-1">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6 reveal">
                <div class="tile h-100">
                    <div class="tile-title">Data validation & certification</div>
                    <div class="tile-text">Automated checks, reconciliation, and quality gates for trusted outputs.</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6 reveal">
                <div class="tile h-100">
                    <div class="tile-title">Metadata & lineage</div>
                    <div class="tile-text">Curated metadata and lineage to improve discovery and governance.</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card compact p-4 mt-3 reveal">
            <h3 class="h5">Performance and reliability</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled d-grid gap-2 mb-0">
                <li>Partitioning strategies and refresh policies for large analytics models.</li>
                <li>SLAs, incident response, and root-cause analysis for production stability.</li>
                <li>Telemetry and standards that make pipelines observable and auditable.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title">Architecture deliverables</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
            Clear standards and artifacts that accelerate delivery and keep the platform consistent.
        </p>
        <div class="row g-3">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6 reveal">
                <div class="card compact p-4 h-100">
                    <h3 class="h5">Reference designs</h3>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled d-grid gap-2 mb-0">
                        <li>Data contracts, source-to-target mappings, and canonical models.</li>
                        <li>Security boundaries, networking posture, and access patterns.</li>
                        <li>Operational runbooks for ingestion, failure handling, and recovery.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-6 reveal">
                <div class="card compact p-4 h-100">
                    <h3 class="h5">Delivery standards</h3>
                    <ul class="list-unstyled d-grid gap-2 mb-0">
                        <li>Testing, validation, and data quality certification.</li>
                        <li>Observability, alerting, and SLO-driven performance targets.</li>
                        <li>Reusable patterns for APIs, pipelines, and metadata.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card compact p-4 mt-3 reveal">
            <h3 class="h5">Operational scenarios</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled d-grid gap-2 mb-0">
                <li>Backfills, replay processing, and hotfix pipelines with full audit trails.</li>
                <li>Dependency-aware scheduling and upstream/downstream impact analysis.</li>
                <li>Disaster recovery planning with validated restore procedures.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card compact p-4 mt-3 reveal">
            <h3 class="h5">Domain playbooks</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled d-grid gap-2 mb-0">
                <li><strong>HR:</strong> workforce events, pay actions, leave balances, and org hierarchy refreshes.</li>
                <li><strong>Budget:</strong> appropriation rollups, spend tracking, and reconciliation controls.</li>
                <li><strong>Cyber:</strong> asset/vuln feeds, incident enrichment, and compliance reporting.</li>
                <li><strong>Procurement:</strong> vendor activity, contract lifecycle, and spend analytics.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <div class="card p-4 reveal">
            <h3 class="h5">Need a big data platform architect?</h3>
            <p class="mb-2">Let's talk about ingestion, governance, and analytics goals.</p>
            <a class="btn btn-primary" href="mailto:justinraypalmer@gmail.com">Reach out</a>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
